# ── Server-side: per-machine config, secrets, generated data ──
# The pipeline runs from /opt/claude-stats and /var/www/stats (outside the repo); these guards
# catch anything sensitive accidentally landing in the working tree when running from a clone.
# NOTE: exact names / scoped globs only — must NOT match committed templates
# (firmware/secrets.example.py, server/config.example.json, *.template).
config.json
token.txt
peer-token.txt
*token*
*.pat
.env
.git-credentials
*.git-credentials
*credentials*
# generated runtime data + DBs
*.db
*.db.bak
*.bak
*.bak-*
claude-stats.json
live-status.json
claude-limits.json
competitor.json
competition.json
peers/
backups/
# rendered-from-template configs (the *.template files stay tracked; *.conf / *.service don't)
server/nginx/*.conf
*.service
